fields.name: AlwaysServe
fields.description: If Always Serve is enabled, probing for endpoint health will be disabled and endpoints will be included in the traffic routing method.

fields.name: EndpointLocation
fields.description: Specifies the location of the external or nested endpoints when using the 'Performance' traffic routing method.

fields.name: EndpointMonitorStatus
fields.description: The monitoring status of the endpoint.

fields.name: EndpointStatus
fields.description: The status of the endpoint. If the endpoint is Enabled, it is probed for endpoint health and is included in the traffic routing method.

fields.name: GeoMapping
fields.description: The list of countries/regions mapped to this endpoint when using the 'Geographic' traffic routing method. Please consult Traffic Manager Geographic documentation for a full list of accepted values.

fields.name: MinChildEndpoints
fields.description: The minimum number of endpoints that must be available in the child profile in order for the parent profile to be considered available. Only applicable to endpoint of type 'NestedEndpoints'.

fields.name: MinChildEndpointsIPv4
fields.description: The minimum number of IPv4 (DNS record type A) endpoints that must be available in the child profile in order for the parent profile to be considered available. Only applicable to endpoint of type 'NestedEndpoints'.

fields.name: MinChildEndpointsIPv6
fields.description: The minimum number of IPv6 (DNS record type AAAA) endpoints that must be available in the child profile in order for the parent profile to be considered available. Only applicable to endpoint of type 'NestedEndpoints'.

fields.name: Priority
fields.description: The priority of this endpoint when using the 'Priority' traffic routing method. Possible values are from 1 to 1000, lower values represent higher priority. This is an optional parameter.  If specified, it must be specified on all endpoints, and no two endpoints can share the same priority value.

fields.name: Subnets
fields.description: The list of subnets, IP addresses, and/or address ranges mapped to this endpoint when using the 'Subnet' traffic routing method. An empty list will match all ranges not covered by other endpoints.

fields.name: Target
fields.description: The fully-qualified DNS name or IP address of the endpoint. Traffic Manager returns this value in DNS responses to direct traffic to this endpoint.

fields.name: TargetResourceId
fields.description: The Azure Resource URI of the of the endpoint. Not applicable to endpoints of type 'ExternalEndpoints'.

fields.name: Weight
fields.description: The weight of this endpoint when using the 'Weighted' traffic routing method. Possible values are from 1 to 1000.
